Gombe State governor, Muhammad’s Inuwa Yahaya, has commended the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA), for the successes recorded in the maritime industry. The governor who was represented by his Deputy, Dr. Manassah Daniel Jatau, at the NIMASA Corporate Dinner and Merit Award night held in Lagos recently, commended the agency for recognising the contributions of the dedicated staff and stakeholders, pointing out that such gesture would spur them to greater performance, efficiency, and higher productivity. He also congratulated the awardees for the recognition and urged them to consider the award as an incentive and motivation for hard work. The governor presented on behalf of NIMASA, awards of merit to staff who put in 25 years of active and meritorious service. In his remarks, according to a statement by the senior special assistant to the governor on Media and Publicity, Ismaila UBA Misili, the director-general NIMASA, Dakuku Peterside explained that the event was organised to celebrate the best of their staff who have shown selflessness, diligence and dedication towards achieving the visions of the agency. He said it was also to recognise the stakeholders who have distinguished themselves in the Maritime industry during the year. Peterside appreciated the contributions of governors and stakeholders, who have helped in building positive partnership towards a sustainable maritime sector.    Senator Muhammad Danjuma Goje who is also the chairman Senate Committee on Marine Transport, presented the award to staff who put in 30 years of service. Gombe State government’s delegation at the event, included commissioner of Special Duties ,Barr Mela Nunge and special adviser, Abuja Liason , Alhaji Usman Aliyu Garry, among others. 